editorialSummary.text: Retail chain offering home goods, clothing, electronics & more, plus exclusive designer collections.

originalText.text: This location of Target is great!! It's not the largest, but they have a great selection of items and I always seem to find what I need here. The staff are helpful and kind, and the check-out line is never totally inundated with customers (things always move pretty quickly and the wait is never too long). This is a great place to stop for necessities on the Upper West Side/Columbus Avenue!

originalText.text: I stumbled upon this location by mistake.  I was actually going to Michaels however Michaels is now closed.  This Target location is a small as compared to other locations.  I went into Target to search for gems/rhinestones for a project however the store didn’t have any.  I was able to purchase the glue sticks I needed.  The staff were helpful and polite.  The store was very clean.   I noticed the store had self check out, I didn’t see any regular registers.  The store is accessible via public transportation.

originalText.text: I give this Target Store a DOUBLE ZERO!!!!!!  How is it that the cashier has no clue that you can price match an item?  How is it that the only person the Leader on Duty is the only one that knew this?  This store is a JOKE-the size of my living room.  It should be shut down completely.  The first person to assist me helped (with a meek smile), when I approached her a second time after waiting around 20 minutes she looked irritated.  You don't like your job, leave.  Also, cashier Amrita needs to be TRAINED!!!!

originalText.text: Location on 61St Street and Broadway on the upper westside never has anything. Worst selection of products. Specially food. Seems like all other locations get all the good products and this one just gets the scraps.

originalText.text: Would like to give one star, due to CVS pharmacy located inside this Target.  I made an on online appointment and recieved both email and text confirmations for the appointment to have a vaccination.  I arrived at the location as recommended more than 10 minutes early, arrived at 5:45.  I was very puzzled to find all the gates closed at the pharmacy.  I doubled checked to confirm location and time.  Time of vaccination appointment was 6:00 pm.  Location Columbus Square inside Target.  There were schedules posted outside the pharmacy walls stating closing time was 7:00 pm.  I spoke with a Target associate who was busy stocking shelves.  They were very nice and very he was very apologetic.  He told me the pharmacy is never open.  He didn't understand why I was able to make an appoiment, and could not provide me with any additional information about the pharmacy, since it is a entity separate from Target and only rents space from Target.  Contact attempts with both CVS and Target have proven fruitless.  I see how both CVS and Target value their customers.  They don't.
